## 4. HOW TO RUN

| Command | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm install` | Install dependencies |
| `npm run setup` | Interactive wizard → creates `.env` |
| `npm run dev` | Start app + discovery worker (tsx watch, auto-reload) |
| `npm run dev:app` | Start only the main app |
| `npm run dev:discovery` | Start only the discovery worker |
| `npm test` | Run all tests |
| `npm run build` | Compile TypeScript to `dist/` |
| `npm start` | Same as `dev` |
| `npm run lint` | ESLint check |
| `npm run validate:egress` | Phase 0: verify Polymarket + Polygon egress (`docs/plans/egress-validation.md`) |

### Boot sequence
1. `start.cjs` checks for `.env`, runs `setup.cjs` if missing
2. Spawns two parallel processes:
   - Main app: `tsx watch src/index.ts` (port 3001)
   - Discovery worker: `tsx watch src/discovery/discoveryWorker.ts` (port 3002)
3. Main app: `index.ts` → `startAppRuntime()` → Storage init → config validate → wallet init → Express server → CopyTrader → monitoring
4. Discovery worker: separate process, communicates via HTTP to `DISCOVERY_WORKER_URL`

### Dashboard
- `http://localhost:3001` — Win95-style web dashboard
- Manages tracked wallets, trading wallets, trade feed, discovery, configuration

