## 10. TRADE SAFETY INVARIANTS (CRITICAL — NEVER VIOLATE)

These rules protect real money. Violating them has caused actual financial losses.

### 1. No-Repeat Trades: ALWAYS active, ALWAYS recorded
- `Storage.isPositionBlocked` MUST run for EVERY trade (not gated on `noRepeatEnabled`)
- When `noRepeatEnabled` is true, use configured `noRepeatPeriodHours`. When false/undefined, use 5-minute safety minimum
- `Storage.addExecutedPosition` MUST be called after EVERY successful trade
- If the no-repeat storage read fails, BLOCK the trade (fail-safe)

### 2. Concurrency Guard: inFlightTrades.add() BEFORE any await
- `inFlightTrades.add(tradeKey)` and `inFlightTrades.add(compoundKey)` MUST be called IMMEDIATELY after the in-flight check, BEFORE any `await`
- `try/finally` MUST wrap everything after the add to guarantee cleanup
- ZERO async operations between the in-flight check and the add

### 3. USDC Commitment Stop-Loss: Fail-Safe
- If any API call fails inside `getUsageStopLossStatus`, return `active: true` (block trades)
- Position value MUST use `curPrice` (market price), not `avgPrice` (cost basis)

### 4. Wallet Settings: ALL fields passed through
- `parseTradeData` in `walletMonitor.ts` MUST pass ALL wallet settings to `DetectedTrade`
- `enrichFromWallet` in `domeWebSocket.ts` MUST also pass ALL wallet settings
- If a new wallet setting is added, it MUST be added to BOTH locations

### 5. Order Size Safety Cap
- Every trade MUST be checked against max order size (2× configured trade size)
- Check happens AFTER sizing calculation but BEFORE sending to CLOB

### 6. Always Rebuild After Code Changes
- `npm run build` before restart if running compiled code
- Dev mode (`tsx watch`) auto-reloads

